81
00:06:49.149 --> 00:06:54.071
THE HUSBAND

82
00:06:58.659 --> 00:07:01.369
<i>When the heart
rate drops to 40 bpm or lower.</i>

83
00:07:01.370 --> 00:07:04.998
<i>one may experience lightheadedness.
syncope. or loss of consciousness.</i>

84
00:07:05.666 --> 00:07:07.667
<i>However. ironically enough…</i>

85
00:07:07.668 --> 00:07:09.962
<i>…the heart fights to keep beating
until the very end.</i>

86
00:07:26.395 --> 00:07:30.148
<i>While chest pain is the most common
early symptom of a myocardial infarction.</i>

87
00:07:30.149 --> 00:07:33.234
<i>women and diabetics
may display atypical symptoms</i>

88
00:07:33.235 --> 00:07:38.532
<i>such as shortness of breath.
indigestion. or severe fatigue.</i>

89
00:07:39.116 --> 00:07:42.285
<i>Moreover. around 20 to 30%
of patients experience</i>

90
00:07:42.286 --> 00:07:44.454
<i>myocardial infarctions
without any early signs.</i>

91
00:07:44.455 --> 00:07:46.331
<i>So. for an accurate diagnosis. they must…</i>

92
00:08:01.430 --> 00:08:02.806
You didn't have to do that.

93
00:08:12.483 --> 00:08:13.484
Oh.

94
00:08:15.736 --> 00:08:18.113
Hey. you got a minute?

95
00:08:19.239 --> 00:08:20.908
Thanks for the drink.

96
00:08:25.162 --> 00:08:26.497
You're all by yourself again.

97
00:08:27.831 --> 00:08:29.249
Why are you always alone?

98
00:08:32.211 --> 00:08:36.757
You study alone. eat alone.
drink coffee alone…

99
00:08:39.384 --> 00:08:41.845
- It's just comfortable.
- Mmm.

100
00:08:43.972 --> 00:08:45.474
Are you just used to being alone?

101
00:08:46.058 --> 00:08:48.101
Or do you have to be alone
to feel comfortable?

102
00:08:54.983 --> 00:08:56.944
I'll see you around. Taeju.

103
00:08:58.529 --> 00:08:59.530
Hold on.

104
00:09:03.325 --> 00:09:04.785
How do you know my name?

105
00:09:11.083 --> 00:09:12.709
{\an8}KANG TAEJU

106
00:09:39.236 --> 00:09:40.946
<i>Heart rate.</i>

107
00:09:41.530 --> 00:09:45.950
<i>When resting. the human heart beats
around 60 to 100 times per minute.</i>

108
00:09:45.951 --> 00:09:48.035
<i>This is called the resting heart rate.</i>

109
00:09:48.036 --> 00:09:51.873
<i>However. the heart rate may
exceed 100 bpm and remain elevated.</i>

110
00:09:51.874 --> 00:09:55.210
<i>even without any physical activity
or external stimulus.</i>

111
00:09:56.086 --> 00:09:58.589
<i>This is called tachycardia.</i>

112
00:09:59.756 --> 00:10:02.425
<i>On the other hand.
when the heart rate is 60 bpm or lower.</i>

113
00:10:02.426 --> 00:10:04.176
<i>it's called bradycardia.</i>

114
00:10:04.177 --> 00:10:07.513
<i>Both can be signs
of underlying conditions.</i>

115
00:10:07.514 --> 00:10:11.100
<i>including cardiac disorders.
such as arrhythmia or thyroid dysfunction.</i>

116
00:10:11.101 --> 00:10:12.978
<i>so one must be wary of both symptoms.</i>

117
00:10:15.230 --> 00:10:20.776
<i>That said. what is the most common
physical symptom a patient notices</i>

118
00:10:20.777 --> 00:10:24.656
<i>when their heart beats at an abnormal rate
due to tachycardia or bradycardia?</i>

119
00:10:40.297 --> 00:10:41.298
<i>Well…</i>

120
00:10:42.925 --> 00:10:44.843
<i>their heart races.</i>

121
00:10:54.728 --> 00:10:56.563
I'm sharing your umbrella.

122
00:10:58.273 --> 00:10:59.274
How have you been?

123
00:11:00.817 --> 00:11:02.194
What's been going on with you?

124
00:11:03.153 --> 00:11:04.237
What do you mean?

125
00:11:06.615 --> 00:11:09.159
Where have you been for the past few days?

126
00:11:12.120 --> 00:11:13.246
Why do you ask?

127
00:11:14.039 --> 00:11:15.165
I mean. you know.

128
00:11:16.750 --> 00:11:19.127
I was used to seeing you around every day.

129
00:11:19.836 --> 00:11:21.338
So it got me wondering.

130
00:11:24.883 --> 00:11:26.218
Oh.

131
00:11:27.344 --> 00:11:29.762
I was stuck at home with the flu for days.

132
00:11:29.763 --> 00:11:31.807
I actually thought I was going to die.

133
00:11:34.559 --> 00:11:35.560
Flu?

134
00:11:36.144 --> 00:11:37.145
So that's what it was.

135
00:11:38.313 --> 00:11:40.524
- Are you better now?
- Yeah. much better.

136
00:11:42.192 --> 00:11:43.485
Were you worried about me?

137
00:11:48.490 --> 00:11:50.617
I was pretty worried about you.

138
00:11:52.202 --> 00:11:53.203
What?

139
00:11:53.954 --> 00:11:55.539
As I was lying in bed.

140
00:11:56.331 --> 00:12:00.085
all I could think about was.
"I bet he's feeling lonely."

141
00:12:04.673 --> 00:12:07.217
Why would you think that?

142
00:12:07.884 --> 00:12:11.804
Well. I assumed you'd be studying alone.

143
00:12:11.805 --> 00:12:15.267
eating alone.
drinking coffee alone. as always.

144
00:12:16.476 --> 00:12:18.061
But I wasn't around.

145
00:12:19.980 --> 00:12:21.940
I thought that'd make you more lonely.

146
00:12:28.488 --> 00:12:30.782
From the looks of it. I guess I was right.

147
00:12:34.786 --> 00:12:35.787
Thank you.

148
00:12:37.205 --> 00:12:38.206
For what?

149
00:12:41.001 --> 00:12:45.255
You know. for looking out for me. I guess.

150
00:12:46.048 --> 00:12:47.466
I wouldn't call it that.

151
00:12:48.300 --> 00:12:50.634
I don't know. Mmm.

152
00:12:50.635 --> 00:12:52.262
I guess you keep getting to me.

153
00:12:53.847 --> 00:12:55.307
So weird. right?

154
00:12:56.975 --> 00:12:57.976
What do you mean?

155
00:12:59.895 --> 00:13:01.897
How we're on each other's minds.

156
00:13:03.607 --> 00:13:05.442
And we barely know each other.

157
00:13:07.152 --> 00:13:08.320
I think it's weird.

158
00:13:09.112 --> 00:13:11.406
I don't get why I think about you so much.

159
00:13:13.366 --> 00:13:17.537
About how you're always alone.
how you're always eating alone…

160
00:13:18.997 --> 00:13:20.707
But mostly. I keep thinking

161
00:13:22.167 --> 00:13:24.920
how lonely you'd be when I'm not around.

162
00:13:28.381 --> 00:13:30.759
I don't want to think
about any of that anymore.

163
00:13:34.554 --> 00:13:35.889
Will you be my boyfriend?

164
00:14:04.668 --> 00:14:06.628
<i>I'm going to your wife now.</i>

165
00:14:07.921 --> 00:14:10.006
<i>I'm so angry and upset right now</i>

166
00:14:11.091 --> 00:14:13.468
<i>that I'm going to shred her to pieces.</i>

167
00:14:14.970 --> 00:14:17.305
W-Wait. sir. Just…

168
00:14:17.848 --> 00:14:19.139
{\an8}INCOMING CALL
FATHER-IN-LAW

169
00:14:19.140 --> 00:14:22.853
H-Hey! Wait. Wait a minute. sir.

170
00:14:23.436 --> 00:14:26.647
Look. I wasn't able
to reach my father-in-law.

171
00:14:26.648 --> 00:14:28.941
but he's calling me back right now.

172
00:14:28.942 --> 00:14:33.153
I can actually get you the money you want.
I promise. I swear.

173
00:14:33.154 --> 00:14:34.281
Are you kidding?

174
00:14:35.282 --> 00:14:37.033
You want another chance?

175
00:14:38.952 --> 00:14:42.747
I mean. have you no shame at all?

176
00:14:43.248 --> 00:14:45.375
I've given you so many chances already.

177
00:14:46.084 --> 00:14:47.167
You want another one?

178
00:14:47.168 --> 00:14:49.671
Yes. please j-just once.

179
00:14:50.589 --> 00:14:52.966
Give me a chance
to make up for what I've done.

180
00:14:55.760 --> 00:14:57.136
Don't do this. boss.

181
00:14:57.137 --> 00:14:59.889
No. please. wait. Please. sir! Just once!

182
00:14:59.890 --> 00:15:02.641
Please. just give me
one last chance. okay?

183
00:15:02.642 --> 00:15:05.478
Geez. you're making this so hard.

184
00:15:19.326 --> 00:15:21.827
You know. once at my old job.

185
00:15:21.828 --> 00:15:24.915
I made a few mistakes that
I could've been fired over. but I wasn't.

186
00:15:26.166 --> 00:15:28.418
<i>Later. I asked the boss
why he didn't fire me.</i>

187
00:15:29.252 --> 00:15:30.629
<i>and he said…</i>

188
00:15:32.881 --> 00:15:33.882
"Look. man."

189
00:15:34.758 --> 00:15:38.595
"Everyone deserves at least three chances
to be the best version of themselves."

190
00:15:41.222 --> 00:15:44.225
<i>And it's not like harming your wife
will make me feel any better.</i>

191
00:15:45.727 --> 00:15:46.937
So. Mr. Kang?

192
00:15:48.021 --> 00:15:49.855
This really is your last chance.

193
00:15:49.856 --> 00:15:51.232
Right. sir.

194
00:15:52.317 --> 00:15:55.444
I appreciate it. Thank you.
Thank you so much.

195
00:15:55.445 --> 00:15:57.279
<i>I'm giving you a chance.</i>

196
00:15:57.280 --> 00:16:00.699
but there will be compensation
for you breaking my heart. right?

197
00:16:00.700 --> 00:16:03.203
Yes. Of course there will be.

198
00:16:04.120 --> 00:16:05.579
Two billion won.

199
00:16:05.580 --> 00:16:06.581
Pardon?

200
00:16:08.083 --> 00:16:09.166
Two billion.

201
00:16:09.167 --> 00:16:11.294
Geez. is the line bad or something?

202
00:16:12.337 --> 00:16:13.630
<i>No.</i>

203
00:16:14.756 --> 00:16:16.548
I heard you. Two billion won.

204
00:16:16.549 --> 00:16:17.884
<i>I'll give you two hours.</i>

205
00:16:18.760 --> 00:16:20.719
<i>but if you go back on your word.</i>

206
00:16:20.720 --> 00:16:25.517
<i>try to call the cops.
or disappoint me with another dumb stunt…</i>

207
00:16:26.893 --> 00:16:27.894
I assure you.

208
00:16:29.020 --> 00:16:31.106
you will pay for it dearly.

209
00:16:32.440 --> 00:16:34.900
<i>This is your last chance. Don't blow it.</i>

210
00:16:36.486 --> 00:16:38.321
Hello?

211
00:16:46.079 --> 00:16:47.372
Yes. Father.

212
00:16:48.039 --> 00:16:50.625
We need to talk. It's about Seyun.

213
00:17:23.199 --> 00:17:24.200
Huh?

214
00:18:23.635 --> 00:18:26.054
Are you okay. Mother?

215
00:18:28.264 --> 00:18:30.600
How dare he do this to my daughter!

216
00:18:32.644 --> 00:18:34.646
Despicable piece of shit.

217
00:18:37.065 --> 00:18:40.193
I swear to God. I'll rip him to pieces!

218
00:18:42.153 --> 00:18:43.988
This can't be happening.

219
00:18:45.824 --> 00:18:47.241
Kidnapping?

220
00:18:47.242 --> 00:18:48.368
Blackmail?

221
00:18:50.954 --> 00:18:54.165
How could this
be happening to my daughter?

222
00:18:55.250 --> 00:18:56.584
But why?

223
00:18:59.754 --> 00:19:01.881
Is this all he sent?

224
00:19:11.724 --> 00:19:13.059
You got nothing else?

225
00:19:34.414 --> 00:19:36.082
UNKNOWN NUMBER

226
00:19:38.626 --> 00:19:39.711
DELETE

227
00:19:45.717 --> 00:19:47.969
Two billion won in two hours…

228
00:19:51.139 --> 00:19:52.390
Did he demand anything else?

229
00:19:55.560 --> 00:19:58.855
He said he'd hurt Seyun
if we went to the police.

230
00:19:59.564 --> 00:20:01.733
We can't get them involved.
no matter what.

231
00:20:06.362 --> 00:20:08.155
How much time do we have left?

232
00:20:08.156 --> 00:20:11.116
Oh. uh. we've got around
an hour and 25 minutes.

233
00:20:12.202 --> 00:20:15.162
We have to hurry.
I'll make calls to banks.

234
00:20:15.163 --> 00:20:17.457
You take the car and pick up the money.

235
00:20:18.458 --> 00:20:21.251
He may come after the money again.
so you go with him.

236
00:20:21.252 --> 00:20:22.961
Oh. yes. Of course.

237
00:20:22.962 --> 00:20:24.881
Okay. we'll be back.

238
00:20:25.507 --> 00:20:27.591
- Wait. honey. Just a sec.
- Huh?

239
00:20:27.592 --> 00:20:30.303
Come here for a minute.

240
00:20:36.643 --> 00:20:38.810
I'll ask them to arrange that.

241
00:20:41.940 --> 00:20:43.149
Got it.

242
00:20:44.817 --> 00:20:49.072
- Yes. hello? Is this the bank manager?
- We'll take my car.

243
00:21:34.409 --> 00:21:36.744
Father. I have to tell you something.

244
00:21:38.162 --> 00:21:39.747
- The thing is--
- It's you.

245
00:21:40.582 --> 00:21:42.041
This is your fault. isn't it?

246
00:21:45.003 --> 00:21:46.086
What is?

247
00:21:46.087 --> 00:21:48.464
This has to be happening because of you.

248
00:21:49.591 --> 00:21:52.635
What are you… What do you mean by that?

249
00:21:53.386 --> 00:21:57.055
Seyun isn't the type
to go around making enemies.

250
00:21:57.056 --> 00:22:01.936
You were probably acting all arrogant
and crossed the wrong person. Am I right?

251
00:22:03.605 --> 00:22:05.397
You were like that in the past too.

252
00:22:05.398 --> 00:22:08.151
You don't care about anything else
when you think you're right.

253
00:22:09.402 --> 00:22:10.945
You can't have changed.

254
00:22:17.493 --> 00:22:19.287
Well. say something!

255
00:22:19.829 --> 00:22:22.457
I'm asking you
if that's why this is happening!

256
00:22:23.166 --> 00:22:24.249
Damn it!

257
00:22:24.250 --> 00:22:25.751
That piece of…

258
00:22:27.045 --> 00:22:28.463
Crazy bastard.

259
00:22:29.881 --> 00:22:31.174
Give me a break.

260
00:22:31.883 --> 00:22:33.384
Seriously…

261
00:22:54.572 --> 00:22:55.865
Come on…

262
00:23:39.325 --> 00:23:43.787
CHOI HYEONSU
NATIONAL POLICE AGENCY

263
00:23:54.173 --> 00:23:55.299
How are you?

264
00:23:55.925 --> 00:23:59.302
I'm Jang Dosik. Captain
of Major Crimes Unit 1 at Seongjin Police.

265
00:23:59.303 --> 00:24:01.722
I've got a few questions for you.

266
00:24:01.723 --> 00:24:03.891
We don't have much time.
so if you don't mind.

267
00:24:05.810 --> 00:24:07.686
<i>So the kidnapper got in your car.</i>

268
00:24:07.687 --> 00:24:11.189
<i>pretending to be your designated driver.
at around 1:30 a.m.</i>

269
00:24:11.190 --> 00:24:14.776
I feel like I made the call a second ago.
You got here so quickly.

270
00:24:14.777 --> 00:24:18.321
Well. I just happened to be
in the area. so I got here fast.

271
00:24:18.322 --> 00:24:22.910
I guess today's just my lucky day.

272
00:24:23.536 --> 00:24:25.495
<i>Remember what the culprit
looked like?</i>

273
00:24:25.496 --> 00:24:28.374
Any scars. tattoos. or anything
we could use to identify him?

274
00:24:29.751 --> 00:24:32.170
No. nothing really comes to mind.

275
00:24:34.630 --> 00:24:37.258
And you didn't recognize
his voice either?

276
00:24:38.384 --> 00:24:39.885
<i>Hello?</i>

277
00:24:39.886 --> 00:24:41.512
<i>Mr. Kang Taeju?</i>

278
00:24:42.180 --> 00:24:43.680
Yes. speaking. Who's this?

279
00:24:43.681 --> 00:24:45.640
{\an8}<i>I'm the driver
who drove you to your house.</i>

280
00:24:45.641 --> 00:24:46.725
{\an8}UNKNOWN NUMBER

281
00:24:46.726 --> 00:24:49.144
{\an8}<i>Well. early this morning. sir.</i>

282
00:24:49.145 --> 00:24:51.230
I'd never heard his voice before.

283
00:24:52.315 --> 00:24:53.399
And his face…

284
00:24:55.401 --> 00:24:58.738
I don't really remember
what he looks like either.

285
00:25:01.115 --> 00:25:02.199
- Choi.
- Yes. sir?

286
00:25:02.200 --> 00:25:04.534
Secure the security footage
around the area.

287
00:25:04.535 --> 00:25:05.536
<i>I'm on it.</i>

288
00:25:08.372 --> 00:25:10.124
<i>The kidnapper could call
any minute now.</i>

289
00:25:10.792 --> 00:25:13.418
<i>We'll be tracking his location
in real time.</i>

290
00:25:13.419 --> 00:25:16.254
<i>so try to drag it out as much as possible.</i>

291
00:25:16.255 --> 00:25:19.299
<i>Culprits like him
like to feel like they're in charge.</i>

292
00:25:19.300 --> 00:25:21.594
<i>so try not to provoke him in any way.</i>

293
00:25:22.637 --> 00:25:24.429
- <i>Okay.</i>
- As for you two.

294
00:25:24.430 --> 00:25:26.389
never interfere or get worked up.

295
00:25:26.390 --> 00:25:29.226
If he catches on.
it'll put your daughter in danger.

296
00:25:31.979 --> 00:25:33.271
Understood.

297
00:25:33.272 --> 00:25:35.316
I appreciate your cooperation.

298
00:25:43.074 --> 00:25:44.951
Why did you call the police?

299
00:25:45.827 --> 00:25:48.496
I told you it would put Seyun in danger.

300
00:25:49.121 --> 00:25:50.665
I thought I'd made that clear.

301
00:25:51.249 --> 00:25:54.377
What. are we supposed to listen
to whatever this guy says?

302
00:25:55.127 --> 00:25:59.131
Of course he tells you not to call them.
He doesn't want to get caught.

303
00:26:00.341 --> 00:26:02.926
You don't understand.
This guy is extremely dangerous.

304
00:26:02.927 --> 00:26:05.179
That's why we called the police.

305
00:26:05.763 --> 00:26:07.682
You're not getting it. This guy…

306
00:26:09.225 --> 00:26:11.811
He's completely insane.

307
00:26:16.524 --> 00:26:19.484
He's a total psycho.

308
00:26:19.485 --> 00:26:22.320
All the more reason we need the police.

309
00:26:22.321 --> 00:26:24.406
We can't deal with him on our own.

310
00:26:24.407 --> 00:26:25.699
No. you don't get it!

311
00:26:26.909 --> 00:26:29.661
You're just putting Seyun
in more danger right now!

312
00:26:29.662 --> 00:26:32.582
You will not speak to my wife that way!

313
00:26:34.417 --> 00:26:36.043
She's my own daughter.

314
00:26:36.627 --> 00:26:37.628
You got that?

315
00:26:38.504 --> 00:26:41.382
I'm the one
who's the most desperate to get her back!

316
00:26:45.261 --> 00:26:46.262
Listen. Taeju.

317
00:26:47.054 --> 00:26:49.806
You've been in the palm of his hand.

318
00:26:49.807 --> 00:26:51.642
so you aren't thinking straight.

319
00:26:52.268 --> 00:26:54.937
This is where you have to
let us handle things.

320
00:26:55.521 --> 00:26:57.063
And don't get in the way!

321
00:26:57.064 --> 00:27:00.067
You have no idea what this guy's like.

322
00:27:02.528 --> 00:27:05.072
You just don't know
because you haven't dealt with him.

323
00:27:05.740 --> 00:27:07.908
Sir? I know this is tough.

324
00:27:08.492 --> 00:27:10.494
but you need to stay calm.

325
00:27:11.120 --> 00:27:12.121
Okay?

326
00:27:13.247 --> 00:27:14.248
Yeah.

327
00:27:54.747 --> 00:27:55.830
Anyone there?

328
00:27:55.831 --> 00:27:58.625
Please let me out of here!

329
00:27:58.626 --> 00:28:00.586
Let me out of here!

330
00:28:03.839 --> 00:28:04.965
Hey!

331
00:28:17.561 --> 00:28:19.021
Are you okay?

332
00:28:23.109 --> 00:28:24.694
Are you hurt at all?

333
00:28:26.821 --> 00:28:28.239
Who's there?

334
00:28:29.365 --> 00:28:31.242
I bet you're pretty confused.

335
00:28:34.078 --> 00:28:35.204
Who the hell are you?

336
00:28:35.996 --> 00:28:36.997
What do you want?

337
00:28:37.665 --> 00:28:41.293
Don't make loud noises.
You'll be in trouble.

338
00:28:45.131 --> 00:28:47.967
What the hell are you saying?

339
00:28:48.884 --> 00:28:52.680
Be quiet! You'll get us both in trouble.

340
00:28:55.725 --> 00:28:56.851
Huh?

341
00:29:13.242 --> 00:29:14.452
Hey.

342
00:29:16.746 --> 00:29:18.748
Excuse me. what did you just say?

343
00:29:19.790 --> 00:29:23.169
We'll get in trouble
with the guy who locked us up here.

344
00:29:26.547 --> 00:29:28.798
Are you locked up against your will too?

345
00:29:34.513 --> 00:29:38.808
Hey. how long
have you been locked up in here?

346
00:29:38.809 --> 00:29:40.310
There's no time.

347
00:29:40.311 --> 00:29:42.313
I'm running out of time.

348
00:29:43.814 --> 00:29:45.483
What does that mean?

349
00:29:46.734 --> 00:29:51.071
When the girl in the red hood
gets swallowed by the snow…

350
00:29:51.822 --> 00:29:55.200
By the pale white snow…
It's all over for me.

351
00:29:55.201 --> 00:29:56.243
It's over.

352
00:29:58.496 --> 00:29:59.830
Hey.

353
00:30:00.873 --> 00:30:05.294
Once she's completely
swallowed. I'll be done for.

354
00:30:31.487 --> 00:30:34.782
He might video call you again.
so you'll sit here alone.

355
00:30:35.407 --> 00:30:36.867
- Hey. Park.
- Yes. sir.

356
00:30:38.661 --> 00:30:42.914
We'll be monitoring in real-time.
so just try to focus on the call.

357
00:30:42.915 --> 00:30:45.125
And try to drag it out
as long as possible.

358
00:30:45.876 --> 00:30:48.462
I know you're nervous.
but your wife's life is on the line.

359
00:30:49.046 --> 00:30:50.798
You have to keep it together. all right?

360
00:30:51.882 --> 00:30:53.925
- Yeah.
- Two minutes left.

361
00:30:53.926 --> 00:30:56.386
- Oh. take them to their room.
- On it.

362
00:30:56.387 --> 00:30:57.429
This way.

363
00:31:01.851 --> 00:31:03.978
Let's just focus on saving Seyun.

364
00:31:05.354 --> 00:31:07.439
Okay?

365
00:31:10.693 --> 00:31:11.735
Don't mess this up.

366
00:31:13.445 --> 00:31:14.446
Yes. sir.

367
00:31:58.866 --> 00:32:01.159
INCOMING VIDEO CALL
UNKNOWN NUMBER

368
00:32:06.790 --> 00:32:09.335
INCOMING VIDEO CALL
UNKNOWN NUMBER

369
00:32:12.379 --> 00:32:13.380
Hello?

370
00:32:16.050 --> 00:32:17.134
<i>It's you. isn't it?</i>

371
00:32:18.469 --> 00:32:20.136
Where are you. Mr. Kang?

372
00:32:20.137 --> 00:32:22.805
Oh. I'm at my in-laws' house right now.

373
00:32:22.806 --> 00:32:24.265
In-laws?

374
00:32:24.266 --> 00:32:25.516
<i>Yeah. I mean.</i>

375
00:32:25.517 --> 00:32:29.854
they managed to prepare the money.

376
00:32:29.855 --> 00:32:32.690
<i>And I didn't want to take off
with so much money.</i>

377
00:32:48.123 --> 00:32:49.332
You got him?

378
00:32:49.333 --> 00:32:50.667
LIVE TRACKING MAP

379
00:32:50.668 --> 00:32:51.794
He's in Mangok-dong.

380
00:32:52.836 --> 00:32:55.339
- Send the squad over to Mangok-dong.
- Copy that.

381
00:32:59.218 --> 00:33:00.719
Huh?

382
00:33:01.220 --> 00:33:02.596
What's going on?

383
00:33:04.223 --> 00:33:06.891
Something's wrong.
It says he's in Useong-dong now.

384
00:33:06.892 --> 00:33:08.602
You said Mangok-dong.

385
00:33:09.812 --> 00:33:10.813
He's moving again.

386
00:33:11.772 --> 00:33:14.817
- He's in Jonghaeng-dong.
- What the hell are you talking about?

387
00:33:15.317 --> 00:33:17.819
He's bouncing the signal
with some kind of hacking tool.

388
00:33:17.820 --> 00:33:19.321
Well. do something about it!

389
00:33:28.288 --> 00:33:29.289
Hello?

390
00:33:30.749 --> 00:33:32.418
Anybody else at home?

391
00:33:33.711 --> 00:33:35.713
No. I'm here on my own.

392
00:33:37.089 --> 00:33:39.425
So you're the only one
on the line right now?

393
00:33:40.050 --> 00:33:41.135
Yes. that's right.

394
00:33:43.804 --> 00:33:45.639
So you're saying…

395
00:33:46.432 --> 00:33:49.601
I can say whatever I want.
since it's just you and me. right?

396
00:33:51.895 --> 00:33:52.896
Yeah. I'd say so.

397
00:33:53.605 --> 00:33:57.025
But first. don't you want to see the cash?

398
00:33:57.026 --> 00:33:58.109
Mr. Kang.

399
00:33:58.110 --> 00:33:59.862
Take a look. It's all here.

400
00:34:00.612 --> 00:34:03.781
<i>No messing around this time.
I got it all in cash right…</i>

401
00:34:03.782 --> 00:34:05.367
Mr. Kang Taeju!

402
00:34:11.707 --> 00:34:13.876
Yeah.

403
00:34:19.673 --> 00:34:21.425
Switch to the back camera for me.

404
00:34:23.218 --> 00:34:24.553
But why?

405
00:34:25.345 --> 00:34:27.639
Just switch it for me. all right?

406
00:34:34.855 --> 00:34:35.981
There you go.

407
00:34:40.986 --> 00:34:44.114
We're going to go through every nook
and cranny in the house.

408
00:34:44.990 --> 00:34:46.575
<i>Do as I tell you.</i>

409
00:34:52.498 --> 00:34:54.041
Okay. right there.

410
00:34:54.583 --> 00:34:56.752
Pan from left to right.

411
00:34:57.669 --> 00:34:58.712
Okay.

412
00:35:03.133 --> 00:35:04.927
What are you doing? Just do it.

413
00:35:09.473 --> 00:35:11.683
Okay. panning from left to right.

414
00:35:21.944 --> 00:35:23.320
And the other way.

415
00:35:31.245 --> 00:35:32.287
Stop.

416
00:35:33.831 --> 00:35:35.582
What was that noise?

417
00:35:36.875 --> 00:35:38.794
What? I didn't hear anything.

418
00:35:39.461 --> 00:35:41.296
Did you not hear that noise?

419
00:35:43.090 --> 00:35:44.341
No. I didn't.

420
00:35:48.470 --> 00:35:49.555
Oh. is that so?

421
00:35:52.724 --> 00:35:54.518
Turn it to your right.

422
00:35:55.144 --> 00:35:56.478
Okay.

423
00:35:57.187 --> 00:35:59.105
That's your left. boss.

424
00:35:59.106 --> 00:36:02.734
Your right is toward the kitchen.
where the noise came from.

425
00:36:07.823 --> 00:36:08.824
Oh dear…

426
00:36:18.709 --> 00:36:21.462
Keep pointing it that way
and walk toward it.

427
00:36:23.881 --> 00:36:24.965
Okay. got it.

428
00:36:50.073 --> 00:36:51.074
Stop.

429
00:37:00.000 --> 00:37:01.001
Mr. Kang.

430
00:37:02.920 --> 00:37:04.963
Now. turn to your right.

431
00:37:24.691 --> 00:37:26.318
I said. turn around.

432
00:37:40.457 --> 00:37:43.252
- Good Lord. I can't stand this anymore.
- Honey.

433
00:37:44.044 --> 00:37:47.505
Look. kid. Are you trying
to get my daughter back or not?

434
00:37:47.506 --> 00:37:49.131
<i>Honey. don't do this.</i>

435
00:37:49.132 --> 00:37:50.883
<i>We said we'd let him handle it.</i>

436
00:37:50.884 --> 00:37:52.010
<i>Quiet!</i>

437
00:37:53.053 --> 00:37:54.555
Give me that phone.

438
00:37:56.765 --> 00:37:59.183
This is Seyun's father.

439
00:37:59.184 --> 00:38:01.018
The girl you took away.

440
00:38:01.019 --> 00:38:03.896
I was going to hand
my son-in-law the money

441
00:38:03.897 --> 00:38:05.982
and stay quiet in the other room.

442
00:38:05.983 --> 00:38:09.151
but I can't trust him with this anymore.

443
00:38:09.152 --> 00:38:11.905
So from now on. you can talk to me.

444
00:38:13.073 --> 00:38:14.324
<i>Put him back on.</i>

445
00:38:14.908 --> 00:38:16.826
Trust me. young man.

446
00:38:16.827 --> 00:38:19.496
It'd be much easier if you talked to me.

447
00:38:20.539 --> 00:38:24.584
<i>This deal is between Mr. Kang and me.
and he's the only one I'll speak to.</i>

448
00:38:24.585 --> 00:38:27.044
Well. it's my daughter and my money!

449
00:38:27.045 --> 00:38:29.088
I'd listen if I were you.

450
00:38:29.089 --> 00:38:31.048
You can talk to me. all right?

451
00:38:31.049 --> 00:38:32.508
Hey. old man!

452
00:38:32.509 --> 00:38:34.218
<i>What? "Old man"?</i>

453
00:38:34.219 --> 00:38:35.970
I said put Mr. Kang back on.

454
00:38:35.971 --> 00:38:38.639
<i>You little… Look here. punk!</i>

455
00:38:38.640 --> 00:38:41.559
I get that you're a criminal.
but show some respect!

456
00:38:41.560 --> 00:38:43.352
How dare you!

457
00:38:43.353 --> 00:38:45.230
What the hell…

458
00:38:45.897 --> 00:38:47.690
Have you lost your mind. pops?

459
00:38:47.691 --> 00:38:50.109
What did you call me?

460
00:38:50.110 --> 00:38:52.778
You little… How dare you!

461
00:38:52.779 --> 00:38:56.825
<i>Uh. sir? Why don't you talk to me?</i>

462
00:38:57.534 --> 00:38:58.827
What do you want. lady?

463
00:39:00.078 --> 00:39:03.164
Fine. go on if you want
your precious daughter to die…

464
00:39:03.165 --> 00:39:05.958
<i>Here's an extra billion won.</i>

465
00:39:05.959 --> 00:39:08.336
<i>If you let my daughter go.</i>

466
00:39:08.337 --> 00:39:11.297
<i>you can have this
on top of the original two billion.</i>

467
00:39:11.298 --> 00:39:14.008
That's three billion won in total.

468
00:39:14.009 --> 00:39:18.012
Hold on. so if I bring you
your daughter right now.

469
00:39:18.013 --> 00:39:20.097
you'll give me three billion won?

470
00:39:20.098 --> 00:39:21.767
<i>Yeah. that's right.</i>

471
00:39:23.268 --> 00:39:26.188
But we want her back within an hour.

472
00:39:27.898 --> 00:39:28.982
<i>After an hour.</i>

473
00:39:29.733 --> 00:39:31.901
I'm taking off 100 million
every five minutes.

474
00:39:31.902 --> 00:39:32.944
No.

475
00:39:34.488 --> 00:39:36.114
So what you're saying is.

476
00:39:36.657 --> 00:39:38.949
<i>if I just bring you your daughter
within the hour.</i>

477
00:39:38.950 --> 00:39:42.870
that three billion won can all be mine?

478
00:39:42.871 --> 00:39:45.832
<i>The final amount will
depend on what you decide to do.</i>

479
00:39:46.416 --> 00:39:49.836
Uh… One hour. three billion?

480
00:39:53.465 --> 00:39:55.676
I'll be in touch within an hour.

481
00:39:56.301 --> 00:39:58.386
I hope you keep your promise. ma'am.

482
00:39:58.387 --> 00:40:00.305
It's currently 4:15 p.m.

483
00:40:01.014 --> 00:40:02.348
One hour. for three billion.

484
00:40:02.349 --> 00:40:03.600
Keep that in mind.

485
00:40:16.154 --> 00:40:17.322
Three billion?

486
00:40:31.920 --> 00:40:33.046
Hey.

487
00:40:36.758 --> 00:40:38.552
Can you not hear me?

488
00:42:54.229 --> 00:42:55.230
Are you all right?

489
00:42:56.731 --> 00:42:57.816
Careful there.

490
00:42:58.483 --> 00:42:59.901
You'll break your ankle.

491
00:43:01.194 --> 00:43:03.737
I wouldn't want my guest to get hurt.

492
00:43:06.700 --> 00:43:11.621
You know. I was really touched
by your mother's love for you.

493
00:43:13.290 --> 00:43:14.666
My mom?

494
00:43:17.377 --> 00:43:20.630
She's an incredibly generous lady.

495
00:43:22.674 --> 00:43:24.592
No. what am I even saying?

496
00:43:24.593 --> 00:43:26.052
You ready?

497
00:43:30.098 --> 00:43:33.476
Are you ready to say hi to your family?

498
00:43:39.399 --> 00:43:41.067
INCOMING VIDEO CALL
UNKNOWN NUMBER

499
00:43:42.527 --> 00:43:45.488
What? It's been nowhere near an hour.

500
00:43:47.198 --> 00:43:49.367
Ma'am. just do
what you did earlier. Be calm.

501
00:44:03.548 --> 00:44:04.633
UNKNOWN NUMBER

502
00:44:05.133 --> 00:44:06.216
<i>Mom!</i>

503
00:44:06.217 --> 00:44:07.302
Seyun!

504
00:44:08.261 --> 00:44:10.639
Oh. Seyun… Se…

505
00:44:11.264 --> 00:44:13.808
You okay. sweetie? Are you hurt?

506
00:44:14.893 --> 00:44:16.686
<i>I'm okay.</i>

507
00:44:17.354 --> 00:44:20.105
Oh. look at you. you poor thing.

508
00:44:20.106 --> 00:44:21.565
Seyun…

509
00:44:21.566 --> 00:44:23.651
- You got him yet?
- I'll take care of it.

510
00:44:23.652 --> 00:44:25.694
Now it says he's in Gansu. China.

511
00:44:25.695 --> 00:44:27.279
Hang in there. okay?

512
00:44:27.280 --> 00:44:28.949
- Se-Seyun…
- <i>Okay.</i>

513
00:44:30.533 --> 00:44:31.909
Sir?

514
00:44:31.910 --> 00:44:35.329
<i>Now you've seen
that your daughter's okay. right?</i>

515
00:44:35.330 --> 00:44:40.251
Where do we go? Tell us.
and we'll be there with the money.

516
00:44:41.211 --> 00:44:42.253
<i>No. it's fine.</i>

517
00:44:43.338 --> 00:44:46.715
<i>I'll take care of everything. ma'am.
Don't worry about a thing.</i>

518
00:44:46.716 --> 00:44:48.301
<i>Just stay comfortable at home.</i>

519
00:44:51.930 --> 00:44:54.391
<i>Sit on your comfortable couch</i>

520
00:44:55.392 --> 00:44:58.102
<i>and watch your precious daughter die!</i>

521
00:44:58.103 --> 00:45:01.230
- Seyun!
- Seyun!

522
00:45:01.231 --> 00:45:02.731
- Wait!
- No!

523
00:45:02.732 --> 00:45:06.610
- Sir! Please. sir!
- No…

524
00:45:06.611 --> 00:45:07.820
Why are you doing this?

525
00:45:07.821 --> 00:45:10.907
<i>Just because you're rich.
you think you can mock me?</i>

526
00:45:11.658 --> 00:45:14.035
<i>No! Not at all!</i>

527
00:45:16.496 --> 00:45:18.789
- No!
- That's not true!

528
00:45:18.790 --> 00:45:20.667
- Stop!
- It's not like that!

529
00:45:21.167 --> 00:45:22.251
No!

530
00:45:24.170 --> 00:45:26.964
- Please… I'm sorry!
- Seyun…

531
00:45:26.965 --> 00:45:29.800
You're sorry?
Well. sorry's not going to cut it.

532
00:45:29.801 --> 00:45:32.429
<i>- Please! Please don't! Stop it!
- Let her go!</i>

533
00:45:34.264 --> 00:45:36.932
- No. you can't! Please don't do this!
- No. stop it!

534
00:45:36.933 --> 00:45:38.976
- Seyun!
- Honey!

535
00:45:45.608 --> 00:45:49.361
- No! Seyun!
- Seyun…

536
00:45:49.362 --> 00:45:51.822
Please…

537
00:45:51.823 --> 00:45:53.992
- Please… No.
- Seyun…

538
00:45:58.288 --> 00:45:59.748
No…

539
00:46:12.594 --> 00:46:13.928
Seyun.

540
00:46:19.350 --> 00:46:20.560
Seyun…

541
00:46:21.936 --> 00:46:24.563
- Se-Se-Seyun?
- Seyun…

542
00:46:24.564 --> 00:46:26.900
<i>Open your eyes. Seyun.</i>

543
00:46:32.489 --> 00:46:36.618
Se-Seyun. wake up. please.

544
00:46:39.329 --> 00:46:40.371
Honey…

545
00:46:45.585 --> 00:46:46.878
Honey…

546
00:46:47.629 --> 00:46:48.922
Honey…

547
00:46:53.009 --> 00:46:54.760
You bastard!

548
00:46:54.761 --> 00:46:56.888
I'm going to kill you!

549
00:46:57.388 --> 00:47:00.683
I'm… I'm going to…

550
00:47:01.392 --> 00:47:06.481
I'm going to find you
and tear you to pieces. you bastard!

551
00:47:14.531 --> 00:47:15.949
Huh?

552
00:47:16.908 --> 00:47:18.826
Se-Seyun?

553
00:47:18.827 --> 00:47:20.160
Se-Seyun!

554
00:47:23.289 --> 00:47:26.375
Look. she's still alive!

555
00:47:26.376 --> 00:47:28.210
Seyun!

556
00:47:28.211 --> 00:47:30.337
Seyun!

557
00:47:30.338 --> 00:47:31.922
- Seyun.
- Honey. she's still alive.

558
00:47:31.923 --> 00:47:34.592
- Can you… Can you hear me?
- Seyun!

559
00:47:35.301 --> 00:47:36.469
<i>Mr. Kang.</i>

560
00:47:38.304 --> 00:47:40.055
<i>Mr. Kang Taeju!</i>

561
00:47:40.056 --> 00:47:41.807
Wait a second. I…

562
00:47:41.808 --> 00:47:44.643
- What do I do?
- I got it…

563
00:47:44.644 --> 00:47:46.019
Ah. ah. uh.

564
00:47:46.020 --> 00:47:49.231
Yes. sir. It's me again. Please go on.

565
00:47:49.232 --> 00:47:50.233
<i>Listen.</i>

566
00:47:51.025 --> 00:47:53.861
<i>You just had to give me
the money you promised. simple as that.</i>

567
00:47:53.862 --> 00:47:54.945
Right.

568
00:47:54.946 --> 00:47:57.489
<i>Why do you keep making it so complicated?</i>

569
00:47:57.490 --> 00:47:58.740
<i>I made this clear.</i>

570
00:47:58.741 --> 00:48:00.034
I said…

571
00:48:00.994 --> 00:48:03.328
I said I'd only talk to you.

572
00:48:03.329 --> 00:48:05.789
but you put those fossils
in charge of the situation.

573
00:48:05.790 --> 00:48:07.416
We're sorry.

574
00:48:07.417 --> 00:48:10.669
I-I'm sorry. I really am.

575
00:48:10.670 --> 00:48:13.548
<i>I said I hate it
when people make things complicated.</i>

576
00:48:14.132 --> 00:48:18.636
<i>And I told you not to call the cops.
but you got not one.</i>

577
00:48:19.179 --> 00:48:24.392
not two. but four pigs
in the house and lied about it.

578
00:48:25.185 --> 00:48:27.269
- He's watching us.
- <i>Why are you doing this to me?</i>

579
00:48:27.270 --> 00:48:28.812
He might have an accomplice.

580
00:48:28.813 --> 00:48:30.355
- Go look outside.
- I'm on it.

581
00:48:30.356 --> 00:48:32.942
- I'm sorry. it's all my fault!
- Oh. God.

582
00:48:34.110 --> 00:48:37.029
<i>Did you really think
you could fool me that easily?</i>

583
00:48:37.030 --> 00:48:39.448
No. it's not like that.

584
00:48:39.449 --> 00:48:41.742
<i>This is just a misunderstanding.</i>

585
00:48:41.743 --> 00:48:44.286
My wife's parents called the cops
out of desperation

586
00:48:44.287 --> 00:48:47.456
because they had no idea
about the situation. I had no choice!

587
00:48:47.457 --> 00:48:50.709
- Yes. We're sorry.
- <i>Excuses.</i>

588
00:48:50.710 --> 00:48:53.880
Stupid excuses! I'm sick and tired of it!

589
00:48:54.839 --> 00:48:58.425
I just trusted you

590
00:48:58.426 --> 00:49:01.804
and did exactly what you asked me to do.

591
00:49:02.972 --> 00:49:05.558
<i>So why are you doing this to me?</i>

592
00:49:06.142 --> 00:49:08.770
<i>I'm getting nothing but bullshit from you.</i>

593
00:49:09.354 --> 00:49:11.480
<i>You just couldn't
bring yourself to pay me?</i>

594
00:49:11.481 --> 00:49:13.524
Is that why you're doing this?

595
00:49:14.901 --> 00:49:17.778
No. Not at all.
Absolutely nothing like that.

596
00:49:17.779 --> 00:49:18.821
<i>Listen to me.</i>

597
00:49:20.323 --> 00:49:22.950
<i>You're going to pay
for disappointing me until the end.</i>

598
00:49:22.951 --> 00:49:26.662
- No! You can't!
- No!

599
00:49:26.663 --> 00:49:28.538
- No!
- Seyun! No!

600
00:49:28.539 --> 00:49:31.167
You didn't keep up
your end of the deal. boss.

601
00:49:32.377 --> 00:49:33.920
And now. your wife's going to die.

602
00:49:35.588 --> 00:49:37.882
- No. please.
- <i>Hey. Kang Taeju.</i>

603
00:49:39.592 --> 00:49:40.885
This is on you.

604
00:49:41.844 --> 00:49:42.928
CALL ENDED

605
00:49:44.013 --> 00:49:45.597
- Sir! Please!
- Seyun.

606
00:49:45.598 --> 00:49:47.849
Don't do this!

607
00:49:47.850 --> 00:49:50.353
Oh. Seyun!

608
00:49:50.853 --> 00:49:53.773
No. Seyun!

609
00:49:55.566 --> 00:49:58.403
This is my fault…

610
00:50:10.164 --> 00:50:12.125
Hey. play that last bit back.

611
00:50:12.709 --> 00:50:13.835
Yes. sir.

612
00:50:16.296 --> 00:50:18.506
<i>…excuses!
I'm sick and tired of it!</i>

613
00:50:19.132 --> 00:50:22.467
<i>I just trusted you</i>

614
00:50:22.468 --> 00:50:25.929
<i>and did exactly what you asked me to do.</i>

615
00:50:25.930 --> 00:50:27.180
"What you asked me to do"?

616
00:50:27.181 --> 00:50:29.517
<i>I'm getting nothing but bullshit from you.</i>

617
00:50:31.019 --> 00:50:33.146
Mr. Kang!

618
00:50:37.191 --> 00:50:41.153
You're under arrest for solicitation
of kidnapping and murder of Ko Seyun.

619
00:50:41.154 --> 00:50:44.072
You have the right to remain silent.
Your words can and will be

620
00:50:44.073 --> 00:50:46.492
used against you.
You have the right to an attorney.

621
00:50:48.578 --> 00:50:49.661
Come on.

622
00:50:49.662 --> 00:50:52.247
What… Why are you doing this?

623
00:50:52.248 --> 00:50:53.749
We'll talk down at the station.

624
00:50:53.750 --> 00:50:55.208
Wh-What on earth is going on?

625
00:50:55.209 --> 00:50:57.587
Wait a minute. Wait.

626
00:50:58.796 --> 00:51:00.131
What the hell are you doing?

627
00:51:01.382 --> 00:51:02.508
We just got a tip.

628
00:51:03.843 --> 00:51:04.969
What tip?

629
00:51:06.054 --> 00:51:08.598
<i>So I said we should get divorced.</i>

630
00:51:09.849 --> 00:51:11.350
<i>But she said she didn't want to.</i>

631
00:51:11.351 --> 00:51:13.686
<i>Well. she said she'd never do it.</i>

632
00:51:14.395 --> 00:51:15.646
<i>Why's that?</i>

633
00:51:16.481 --> 00:51:17.856
<i>Because it's what I want.</i>

634
00:51:17.857 --> 00:51:20.485
<i>She doesn't want to
give me anything I want.</i>

635
00:51:22.528 --> 00:51:24.112
<i>I just trusted you…</i>

636
00:51:24.113 --> 00:51:27.200
<i>…and did exactly what you asked me to do.</i>

637
00:51:28.159 --> 00:51:29.243
Yeah. talk.

638
00:51:30.536 --> 00:51:31.620
What?

639
00:51:31.621 --> 00:51:36.376
<i>Good afternoon.
I have a tip about a renowned neurosurgeon</i>

640
00:51:37.043 --> 00:51:40.922
<i>soliciting the murder of his own wife.</i>

641
00:51:42.382 --> 00:51:46.218
<i>She doesn't want to
give me anything I want.</i>

642
00:51:46.219 --> 00:51:49.304
Wait. isn't that your voice?

643
00:51:49.305 --> 00:51:51.681
<i>I'm out of options now.</i>

644
00:51:51.682 --> 00:51:54.769
Taeju. what am I hearing?

645
00:51:55.478 --> 00:51:57.355
<i>Anyway. that being said…</i>

646
00:52:00.066 --> 00:52:04.445
<i>I want you to get rid of my wife.</i>

647
00:52:05.113 --> 00:52:06.406
<i>What did you say?</i>

648
00:52:07.073 --> 00:52:09.117
<i>Get rid of my wife.</i>

649
00:52:10.618 --> 00:52:11.994
<i>I'll pay you. okay?</i>

650
00:52:13.413 --> 00:52:15.497
<i>I'll pay you 300… No.</i>

651
00:52:15.498 --> 00:52:18.334
<i>I'll pay you 500 million won.</i>

652
00:52:18.918 --> 00:52:20.128
<i>So please.</i>

653
00:52:22.672 --> 00:52:24.589
Father. it's not what it looks like.

654
00:52:24.590 --> 00:52:26.967
- I can explain everything. Believe me!
- Take him.

655
00:52:26.968 --> 00:52:28.385
- Come on.
- What's going on?

656
00:52:28.386 --> 00:52:29.761
Say something!

657
00:52:29.762 --> 00:52:31.930
- Father. I can explain everything!
- Get moving!

658
00:52:31.931 --> 00:52:35.143
You bastard!

659
00:52:37.019 --> 00:52:38.562
- Take him to the station.
- Got it.

660
00:53:34.702 --> 00:53:35.869
SEONGJIN POLICE STATION

661
00:53:35.870 --> 00:53:37.497
TAKING ACCOUNTABILITY
FOR THE PEOPLE

662
00:53:41.375 --> 00:53:42.418
Mr. Kang.

663
00:53:44.420 --> 00:53:46.214
How do you know the kidnapper?

664
00:53:47.423 --> 00:53:48.841
I don't know him.

665
00:53:49.759 --> 00:53:52.344
He showed up when I called for a driver.

666
00:53:52.345 --> 00:53:54.222
So you solicited

667
00:53:55.348 --> 00:53:57.558
a complete stranger to murder your wife?

668
00:53:58.559 --> 00:54:00.436
I never solicited anything.

669
00:54:02.438 --> 00:54:06.942
<i>I want you to get rid of my wife.</i>

670
00:54:06.943 --> 00:54:08.653
<i>What? What did you say?</i>

671
00:54:09.237 --> 00:54:10.987
<i>Get rid of my wife.</i>

672
00:54:10.988 --> 00:54:12.990
<i>I'll pay you. okay?</i>

673
00:54:13.908 --> 00:54:16.409
<i>- I'll pay you 300… No.
- So what did you mean by that?</i>

674
00:54:16.410 --> 00:54:18.995
<i>I'll pay you 500 million won.</i>

675
00:54:18.996 --> 00:54:20.664
- <i>So please.</i>
- Well…

676
00:54:20.665 --> 00:54:25.378
I was drunk out of my mind at that time.

677
00:54:30.299 --> 00:54:35.513
Honestly. I don't really remember.
And I don't know why I said that.

678
00:54:37.348 --> 00:54:39.350
You know where Ms. Ko is. don't you?

679
00:54:40.059 --> 00:54:41.644
Is she with your accomplice?

680
00:54:42.770 --> 00:54:44.271
Mr. Kang Taeju.

681
00:54:44.272 --> 00:54:46.482
Mr. Kang. where's your accomplice?

682
00:54:48.943 --> 00:54:51.069
I really don't know.
I didn't put him up to it.

683
00:54:51.070 --> 00:54:53.029
Tell us. You know where she is!

684
00:54:53.030 --> 00:54:55.283
I said I don't know!

685
00:55:01.372 --> 00:55:04.249
The… Yes. the tip you got.

686
00:55:04.250 --> 00:55:06.209
I'm sure it's from him.

687
00:55:06.210 --> 00:55:09.045
You can just track the IP or something.

688
00:55:09.046 --> 00:55:12.842
IP says that email
came from Nanning. China.

689
00:55:15.678 --> 00:55:17.387
You didn't see this coming. did you?

690
00:55:17.388 --> 00:55:19.139
Your accomplice…

691
00:55:19.140 --> 00:55:22.309
He's way more dangerous than you think.

692
00:55:22.310 --> 00:55:24.478
You're going to end up
taking the fall alone.

693
00:55:28.733 --> 00:55:30.359
Like I told you. I have no idea.

694
00:55:33.696 --> 00:55:35.948
Don't do this. man.

695
00:55:36.699 --> 00:55:37.783
Just be honest.

696
00:55:38.409 --> 00:55:39.869
Where's Ms. Ko?

697
00:55:40.786 --> 00:55:41.787
I don't know.

698
00:55:42.913 --> 00:55:45.291
Just how many times do I have to tell you?

699
00:55:46.083 --> 00:55:48.044
You're losing time here!

700
00:55:49.003 --> 00:55:52.922
Do you have any idea
what a waste of time this is?

701
00:55:52.923 --> 00:55:56.593
This guy is a psycho!
My wife is in danger!

702
00:55:56.594 --> 00:55:57.761
Calm down. Mr. Kang.

703
00:55:57.762 --> 00:56:01.890
I'm serious!
There's no time to be screwing around!

704
00:56:01.891 --> 00:56:03.392
Mr. Kang!

705
00:56:10.483 --> 00:56:11.484
Calm now?

706
00:56:17.698 --> 00:56:20.326
Hey. say something.

707
00:56:21.827 --> 00:56:24.121
Don't leave me here all by myself.

708
00:56:37.635 --> 00:56:40.261
Wash your face off.
And freshen up a little.

709
00:56:40.262 --> 00:56:41.513
That one doesn't work.

710
00:56:41.514 --> 00:56:42.640
Use the next one.

711
00:56:48.771 --> 00:56:49.772
What the hell?

712
00:56:52.108 --> 00:56:55.527
Man. it's about time
they fix this place up.

713
00:56:55.528 --> 00:56:57.655
Nothing works in here.

714
00:57:02.410 --> 00:57:04.244
Oh. hey. Captain Kim.

715
00:57:04.245 --> 00:57:06.622
Yeah. It's been too long.

716
00:57:07.289 --> 00:57:09.290
Oh. that? Yeah. it was really helpful.

717
00:57:09.291 --> 00:57:10.959
Take your time. okay?

718
00:57:10.960 --> 00:57:13.963
Right. I was going to come and see you.

719
00:57:26.392 --> 00:57:28.017
Damn it.

720
00:57:39.405 --> 00:57:41.573
- What the hell. man?
- Hey. come over here!

721
00:57:41.574 --> 00:57:43.158
What's that? No. not you.

722
00:57:43.159 --> 00:57:45.244
SEONGJIN POLICE STATION

723
00:57:47.788 --> 00:57:50.291
I don't have time to waste here.

724
00:57:51.792 --> 00:57:54.837
I didn't do it. but everyone thinks I did.

725
00:57:56.338 --> 00:57:58.257
No one believes me.

726
00:57:59.383 --> 00:58:00.676
Who would?

727
00:58:04.972 --> 00:58:06.390
No one believes you.

728
00:58:07.850 --> 00:58:10.102
Why would anyone believe you. Mr. Kang?

729
00:58:15.399 --> 00:58:16.609
Who are you?

730
00:58:21.906 --> 00:58:22.948
What do you want?

731
00:58:28.204 --> 00:58:29.788
I said. who are you?

732
00:58:30.331 --> 00:58:35.461
I'm the only one who knows
you didn't plot your wife's death.

733
00:58:37.546 --> 00:58:38.547
What?

734
00:58:48.015 --> 00:58:52.936
THE HUSBAND

735
00:59:32.977 --> 00:59:36.521
{\an8}<i>If you want to find your wife.
come to 543-7. Shinyu-dong.</i>

736
00:59:36.522 --> 00:59:38.273
{\an8}<i>Remember. Get there by 11 p.m.</i>

737
00:59:38.274 --> 00:59:39.399
{\an8}<i>Mr. Kang!</i>

738
00:59:39.400 --> 00:59:40.526
{\an8}Get him!

739
00:59:41.026 --> 00:59:44.612
{\an8}<i>Police took over 20 minutes
to arrive. allowing the suspect to escape.</i>

740
00:59:44.613 --> 00:59:47.865
{\an8}How's my brother the suspect
when his wife's been kidnapped?

741
00:59:47.866 --> 00:59:48.950
{\an8}<i>It wasn't you. was it?</i>

742
00:59:48.951 --> 00:59:51.452
{\an8}<i>Seyun will be in more danger
if I stay at the station.</i>

743
00:59:51.453 --> 00:59:52.579
{\an8}Stay away!

744
00:59:52.580 --> 00:59:55.541
{\an8}<i>Visual on suspect vehicle.
Requesting backup.</i>

745
00:59:57.334 --> 00:59:59.335
{\an8}<i>This is how much time
you have left.</i>

746
00:59:59.336 --> 01:00:02.547
{\an8}When the sand runs out. you're dead.

747
01:00:02.548 --> 01:00:04.466
{\an8}<i>I have to save Seyun.</i>

748
01:00:04.967 --> 01:00:06.969
{\an8}Translated by Hyun Sik Yoon

748
01:00:07.305 --> 01:01:07.753
